{
  "stem": "1860.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 259.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Men were afraid that they'll be caught for the forced labor, but nothing would happen to women.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Nobody imagined that-- what's waiting, what's in store for us.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, we also had papers.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And we wanted to leave, like, two months or two months later.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But the Germans wouldn't let us out.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "So we stayed.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Our bank account was blocked.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "We were left without any money.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And we-- we tried to-- I was the one who was trying to sell anything that was sellable in the house, like musical instruments, book, knickknacks.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And fortunately, there was a-- my mother's cousin by marriage, his name was Abram Banker, who was the owner of the Emalia enamelware factory.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And he was helping us out financially, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] saying always that if my father's survives the war, then-- if we all survive the war, then my father will certainly return all the money to him.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And my father did.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This is still 1941.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I am 15. 14, 14.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "With my mother and a woman by the name of Teckla, who was a gentile Ukrainian woman.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She was my-- she was a combination of a nanny and a maid.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She came to our house when I was six months old.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I consider her like my second mother.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She was extremely devoted.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And as a matter of fact, when-- when the Germans started raiding our Jewish quarters, the apartments, and the homes and the apartments, looking for valuables and anything that they wanted to help themselves to, this Teckla used to walk out of the apartment.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My mother had beautiful jewelry, so she sewed it into a corset.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And every time there was a search, Teckla would put it on and under different pretexts, would leave the apartment.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
